00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:19,446
in documentaries about me,

265
00:11:19,513 --> 00:11:20,757
in the Campbell's Soup
commercial

266
00:11:20,781 --> 00:11:22,950
my mom did without my knowledge.

267
00:11:23,016 --> 00:11:24,451
Oh, Grayson,

268
00:11:24,518 --> 00:11:26,453
growing up with nothing
but football

269
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,188
can't have been healthy.

270
00:11:28,255 --> 00:11:30,424
No, no, I'm good.

271
00:11:30,524 --> 00:11:32,226
Gimme that back!

272
00:11:32,326 --> 00:11:33,961
Starters eat before scrubs!

273
00:11:34,061 --> 00:11:35,829
Everybody knows that!

274
00:11:42,669 --> 00:11:45,939
You know, I'm beginning to see
the appeal of football.

275
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,908
Hit him again!

276
00:11:48,008 --> 00:11:49,610
Kids, behave!

277
00:11:51,778 --> 00:11:54,681
In a family,
we do not steal food.

278
00:11:54,781 --> 00:11:55,983
- But...
- No buts.

279
00:11:56,049 --> 00:11:57,660
Just because there aren't
coaches and minders

280
00:11:57,684 --> 00:12:01,188
watching your every move doesn't
mean you can act selfishly.

281
00:12:01,288 --> 00:12:04,391
In a family, you don't do you.

282
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:05,492
You do...

283
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:06,559
others?

284
00:12:06,627 --> 00:12:07,995
And don't you forget it.

285
00:12:08,095 --> 00:12:10,397
Now, boys, clear the table.

286
00:12:11,598 --> 00:12:13,500
Bust. Bust. Bust.

287
00:12:14,301 --> 00:12:16,503
You sure the rookie
doesn't mind sharing?

288
00:12:16,603 --> 00:12:18,639
Maggie loves company.

289
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:20,340
Um, Mrs. Marge,

290
00:12:20,407 --> 00:12:21,975
do-do you think
it'd be all right

291
00:12:22,042 --> 00:12:23,644
if I stayed here for a while?

292
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:26,547
I've never been around
a real family before.

293
00:12:26,647 --> 00:12:28,782
Of course you can.

294
00:12:28,882 --> 00:12:30,284
You sure? I'm a lot of work.

295
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:32,719
I need 9,000 calories a day
or I'll die.

296
00:12:32,786 --> 00:12:35,489
So does my husband, silly.

297
00:13:08,488 --> 00:13:09,489
Wow!

298
00:13:09,590 --> 00:13:11,892
I've never seen such
a tiny megachurch.

299
00:13:11,925 --> 00:13:14,828
It's a normal-sized
regular church, Grayson.

300
00:13:15,596 --> 00:13:18,966
Hey, here's a little fuel
for your private jet, Reverend.

301
00:13:19,733 --> 00:13:23,637
When did the faces
on the paper money get so big?

302
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,075
Wow.

303
00:13:28,175 --> 00:13:29,877
My first birthday party.

304
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:31,945
I made you a card.

305
00:13:32,045 --> 00:13:35,048
We're all playing catch.

306
00:13:35,115 --> 00:13:36,617
You've all given me so much.

307
00:13:36,717 --> 00:13:38,018
I have a family now.

308
00:13:38,085 --> 00:13:40,454
A family that's shown me
I don't have to be selfish

309
00:13:40,521 --> 00:13:41,521
to be a success.

310
00:13:41,588 --> 00:13:42,356
Huddle up, team.

311
00:13:42,422 --> 00:13:44,124
Feelings on three!
One, two, three!

312
00:13:44,191 --> 00:13:45,192
Feelings!

313
00:13:45,292 --> 00:13:47,060
Who wants presents?

314
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,562
- I do! I do!
- Ooh, ooh, I do!

315
00:13:48,662 --> 00:13:49,796
- I do! I do!
- Merch!

316
00:13:49,897 --> 00:13:51,798
Try this on, big fella.

317
00:13:53,734 --> 00:13:55,502
Mr. Burns! Mr. Burns!

318
00:13:55,569 --> 00:13:57,070
I'm so glad you came!

319
00:13:57,137 --> 00:13:59,239
Now it's a party, huh, guys?

320
00:13:59,306 --> 00:14:00,941
Oh, I would never miss
the birthday

321
00:14:01,008 --> 00:14:02,943
of football's brashest bad boy.

322
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,244
Now let's head out.

323
00:14:04,311 --> 00:14:07,181
You and I are having
a night on the town.

324
00:14:07,281 --> 00:14:10,017
It's time to party
with Brandyman!

325
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:13,353
Or Do-You-Man? I'm...
Can we decide on a catchphrase?

326
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:15,455
Catchphrase TBD!

327
00:14:15,489 --> 00:14:16,723
Are you nuts?

328
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,258
You do realize that Grayson has

329
00:14:18,325 --> 00:14:21,228
a career-defining
football game tomorrow.

330
00:14:21,295 --> 00:14:24,431
He's gonna go to bed early
after a nice hot bath.

331
00:14:24,565 --> 00:14:27,801
You can try out
the Silly Soap I bought. Huh?

332
00:14:27,901 --> 00:14:29,002
All right!

333
00:14:29,069 --> 00:14:30,804
This man plays a game
for a living

334
00:14:30,904 --> 00:14:33,173
and you infantilize him?

335
00:14:33,307 --> 00:14:37,444
Fine, but your mollycoddling
will have dire consequences.

336
00:14:37,511 --> 00:14:39,446
Mark my words.

337
00:14:39,546 --> 00:14:43,250
Mathers with
his fourth touchdown of the day!

338
00:14:43,317 --> 00:14:45,485
And in a never-before-seen move,

339
00:14:45,552 --> 00:14:48,055
the opposing defense
is resigning en masse

340
00:14:48,121 --> 00:14:50,724
to try their luck
in the Canadian Football League.

341
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:52,192
Good luck, fellas.

342
00:14:52,292 --> 00:14:56,063
There he is! The man I never
thought was a bust for a second!

343
00:14:56,163 --> 00:14:58,065
A 53-point win.

344
00:14:58,131 --> 00:15:00,367
Bet you can't wait to say
something really arrogant.

345
00:15:00,434 --> 00:15:02,369
Just lucky
to have great teammates,

346
00:15:02,469 --> 00:15:03,704
what a game plan,

347
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:06,340
keep my head down and work.

348
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:10,611
But also the greats who paved
the way in this league.

349
00:15:11,912 --> 00:15:13,881
Where's my bad boy?

350
00:15:13,947 --> 00:15:16,149
Come on, son. Be a sore winner.

351
00:15:16,216 --> 00:15:17,885
Make Daddy proud.

352
00:15:17,985 --> 00:15:20,120
Maybe you could call
the other team soft?

353
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:22,556
I mean, it's just us reporters
here. No one will know.

354
00:15:22,656 --> 00:15:25,025
No, sir. I'm just trying
to be the kind of guy

355
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:27,060
who makes a mother proud.

356
00:15:27,127 --> 00:15:28,829
Are you saying...

357
00:15:28,896 --> 00:15:30,430
you're a mama's boy?

358
00:15:30,531 --> 00:15:33,400
I'm the biggest mama's boy
on the planet!

359
00:15:35,002 --> 00:15:36,904
Mmm. Tastes good.

360
00:15:37,004 --> 00:15:39,573
Marge Simpson,
what have you done?

361
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:48,148
You've ruined
our beautiful, arrogant boy!

362
00:15:48,248 --> 00:15:50,884
Ruined? He's happy now.

363
00:15:50,951 --> 00:15:52,719
What's wrong, guys?
Why are you fighting?

364
00:15:52,786 --> 00:15:55,722
Oh, this woman's got you as
twisted as a Cossack's mustache.

365
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:59,293
What happened to the bad boy I
raised up from recent adulthood?

366
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:01,228
Don't listen to him, Grayson.

367
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:04,998
I'm so sorry
I ruined your spokesperson.

368
00:16:05,132 --> 00:16:06,867
He's not just my spokesperson.

369
00:16:06,934 --> 00:16:08,268
He's my spokes-son.

370
00:16:08,335 --> 00:16:10,370
And you stole him from me.

371
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:13,106
You're so merged
with your own selfishness,

372
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:16,577
you don't even identify it
as selfishness anymore.

373
00:16:16,643 --> 00:16:17,744
You're a monster!

374
00:16:17,878 --> 00:16:19,313
And you're winning!

375
00:16:20,848 --> 00:16:22,950
You've got to choose, my boy.

376
00:16:23,016 --> 00:16:24,618
Me or her.

377
00:16:24,685 --> 00:16:27,821
Can't you see
you're tearing me apart?!

378
00:16:27,888 --> 00:16:30,057
I need to grind tape
of blitz protections

379
00:16:30,123 --> 00:16:32,693
against an eight-man box!

380
00:16:47,407 --> 00:16:51,044
I haven't heard
from Grayson in days.

381
00:16:51,144 --> 00:16:54,548
Neither has the NFL Network,
ESPN or Adam Schefter.

382
00:16:54,681 --> 00:16:56,350
The football world
hangs in the balance,

383
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:58,185
waiting for
this rookie phenom quarterback

384
00:16:58,252 --> 00:17:00,487
to choose
between his surrogate parents.

385
00:17:00,587 --> 00:17:04,558
My sources tell me that Mathers
hasn't gone back to Mr. Burns

386
00:17:04,625 --> 00:17:07,194
and that Marge has just
this second finished folding

387
00:17:07,261 --> 00:17:09,930
the sheets Grayson
may never sleep on again.

388
00:17:09,997 --> 00:17:11,765
What sources?

389
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:17,804
What if I never see my special
big football boy again?

390
00:17:17,838 --> 00:17:21,742
Mom, a fancy invitation
came for you.

391
00:17:21,842 --> 00:17:23,443
Grayson sent me a ticket

392
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:26,713
for the Sports Channel's
annual awards show.

393
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:28,849
You're going
to the Sportswardsies?

394
00:17:28,949 --> 00:17:31,051
That's the one night
when pro athletes

395
00:17:31,151 --> 00:17:33,287
finally get to thank
their agents.

396
00:17:33,353 --> 00:17:35,989
And Grayson picked me
as his plus-one,

397
00:17:36,056 --> 00:17:37,624
not Mr. Burns.

398
00:17:37,724 --> 00:17:38,892
You won!

399
00:17:38,992 --> 00:17:40,894
Motherhood won!

400
00:17:40,994 --> 00:17:42,930
Yippee!

401
00:17:44,364 --> 00:17:46,333
All good, all good.

402
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:54,740
- You!
- You!

403
00:17:54,808 --> 00:17:58,011
Wait, I'm supposed
to be sitting next to Grayson.

404
00:17:58,111 --> 00:18:01,014
So am I.
I know what's happening here.

405
00:18:01,114 --> 00:18:03,317
Obviously, our boy
sat us together thinking

406
00:18:03,417 --> 00:18:05,853
we would reach
some sort of rapprochement.

407
00:18:05,953 --> 00:18:07,921
He Parent Trapped us!

408
00:18:07,988 --> 00:18:09,122
Too bad for him...

409
00:18:09,189 --> 00:18:11,358
We're never gonna
see eye to eye.

410
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:12,459
Amen, sister.

411
00:18:12,526 --> 00:18:16,096
A toast
to never-ending animosity.

412
00:18:16,897 --> 00:18:18,565
I'll drink to that.

413
00:18:18,632 --> 00:18:20,400
Enemies forever.

414
00:18:23,103 --> 00:18:24,872
The Sportswardsies are starting.

415
00:18:24,972 --> 00:18:27,007
Kids, have you filled out
your betting sheets?

416
00:18:27,074 --> 00:18:29,309
Look at these categories.

417
00:18:29,409 --> 00:18:30,511
Worst Contract?

418
00:18:30,611 --> 00:18:31,745
Best World Series?

419
00:18:31,845 --> 00:18:33,747
The Donald Sterling
Appalling Owner.

420
00:18:33,847 --> 00:18:35,916
Lifetime Achievement Award?

421
00:18:35,983 --> 00:18:38,118
James Dolan,
James Dolan, James Dolan.

422
00:18:38,252 --> 00:18:41,221
For me, it's all about
Best Stretcher Ride Thumbs-Up.

423
00:18:41,288 --> 00:18:43,590
Most of all,
I'd like to thank Gordo,

424
00:18:43,657 --> 00:18:46,193
who I pay six figures
to carry my trophies.

425
00:18:46,293 --> 00:18:48,729
Gordo, this is for you, buddy.

426
00:18:49,663 --> 00:18:52,299
When we come back,
the Sportswardsy

427
00:18:52,366 --> 00:18:54,501
for Most Inspiring Athlete.

428
00:18:54,568 --> 00:18:57,004
Oh, he's looking
at the wrong camera.

429
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:59,206
He's such a cutie.

430
00:18:59,273 --> 00:19:02,609
How could two people like us,
with all our flaws,

431
00:19:02,743 --> 00:19:04,745
make this perfect creature?

432
00:19:04,811 --> 00:19:06,547
I'm a terrible father.

433
00:19:06,613 --> 00:19:09,816
I should have raised him
to be a man, not a brand.

434
00:19:09,883 --> 00:19:12,953
Ah. Let's promise
we'll do better, Monty.

435
00:19:13,020 --> 00:19:14,421
Together.

436
00:19:14,488 --> 00:19:18,358
The winner
for Most Inspiring Athlete is...

437
00:19:18,492 --> 00:19:19,793
Grayson Mathers.

438
00:19:22,162 --> 00:19:24,965
You all know I've had
some personal struggles lately.

439
00:19:25,032 --> 00:19:28,235
I was losing
the football game of emotions.

440
00:19:28,302 --> 00:19:31,004
But there's one person
who got me through it.

441
00:19:31,071 --> 00:19:32,506
He's talking about you.

442
00:19:32,573 --> 00:19:33,841
You're the nurturer.

443
00:19:33,974 --> 00:19:35,976
But you're his inspiration.

444
00:19:36,043 --> 00:19:37,744
It's got to be you.

445
00:19:39,847 --> 00:19:40,981
And that person is...

446
00:19:41,048 --> 00:19:44,685
my fiancée Kaitlyn!

447
00:19:44,785 --> 00:19:47,321
The three days I've known her
have seemed like a lifetime.

448
00:19:47,387 --> 00:19:50,023
An Instagram model,
a YouTube reactor

449
00:19:50,123 --> 00:19:52,092
and the creator of Yoga Yogurt,

450
00:19:52,159 --> 00:19:54,461
the faith-based yogurt
you eat while yoga-ing.

451
00:19:54,561 --> 00:19:57,331
Kaitlyn is so much more
than a business manager to me.

452
00:19:57,431 --> 00:20:00,033
Though she's that, too!
As of this morning!

453
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:02,870
Hope you can handle
total financial control, baby!

454
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:04,171
Good news, babe!

455
00:20:04,271 --> 00:20:05,772
You're fighting Floyd Mayweather

456
00:20:05,839 --> 00:20:07,841
on a Valentine's Day
pay-per-view!

457
00:20:09,276 --> 00:20:11,011
She's getting me out
of the brandy business,

458
00:20:11,078 --> 00:20:13,080
into something
more wholesome, y'all:

459
00:20:13,146 --> 00:20:16,416
Our new line
of all-ages hard seltzers.

460
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:18,252
@Katilicious _97,

461
00:20:18,318 --> 00:20:20,020
I can't wait to marry you.

462
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:21,522
Tell me there's a prenup.

463
00:20:21,588 --> 00:20:22,588
No prenup!

464
00:20:22,623 --> 00:20:24,191
That's how I roll!

465
00:20:24,258 --> 00:20:26,326
Who wants some seltzers?

466
00:20:26,393 --> 00:20:27,327
Dime for you!

467
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:29,997
And just like that,
we've been replaced.

468
00:20:30,097 --> 00:20:32,833
One day, they're these sweet,
innocent creatures

469
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:34,935
who are totally reliant on you.

470
00:20:35,002 --> 00:20:37,437
Then, suddenly,
it's two weeks later

471
00:20:37,504 --> 00:20:39,606
and they're gone.

472
